== Rice ==

Boil a large #pot{} of @water{to taste} with @salt{to taste} for the rice.

Once boiling add the @Jasmine Rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{12-15%mins}.

Drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pot.

Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

== Prep ==

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced).

Roughly chop the @Mushrooms{250%grams}(roughly chopped).

Trim and thinly slice the @Scallion{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced).

Peel and grate the @Garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) and @Ginger{1}(peeled and grated).

== Toasting the Sesame Seeds ==

Place a pan over medium heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry the @Sesame Seeds{1%sachet} until toasted, stirring regularly.

Remove from the pan and set aside.

> TIP: Watch the sesame seeds closely so they don't burn.

== Marinating the Chicken ==

In a large #bowl{}, mix @Sugar{2%tbsp} (double for 4p), the ginger, garlic, @Soy Sauce{2%sachets}, @BBQ Rub{1%sachet} and half the sesame seeds.

If you've got one, use a #food processor{} to mix to a smooth paste.

Mix the @Diced Irish Chicken Breast{260%grams} through your marinade then allow to sit for ~{5-10%mins}.

== Stir-Frying ==

While the chicken marinates, return your (now empty) pan to high heat with a drizzle of @Oil{to taste}.

Once oil is hot, fry the onion and mushroom until softened, ~{4-5%mins}.

Stir occasionally. Season with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}.

Add the chicken and fry until golden brown and cooked through, ~{8-10%mins}. Turn every 2-3 mins.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

If required, add a splash of water to the pan to loosen.

== To Serve ==

Divide the rice between #bowls{} and top with the chicken bulgogi.

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Garnish with scallions and remaining sesame seeds.